#: ../../../docs/limitations.rst:3
msgid "Limitations"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../docs/limitations.rst:5
msgid ""
"These are the known limitations of the tool compared to rustdoc. If using "
"the tool along with rustdoc, the generated output will differ from that of "
"rustdoc due to these issues."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../docs/limitations.rst:8
msgid "The tool can only document the source code that is parsed by syn_."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../docs/limitations.rst:10
msgid ""
"A major limitation here is not being able to document meta items that are "
"generated by macros, or items whose declarations are otherwise wrapped "
"within a macro invocation. The only way to achieve this would be to rewrite "
"parts of the Rust compiler, and that is far beyond the scope of this tool."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../docs/limitations.rst:14
msgid ""
"Some features that cannot be documented by the tool due to this limitation:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../docs/limitations.rst:16
msgid "Items defined using macros or item definitions that are inside a macro."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../docs/limitations.rst:17
msgid "Derived traits, auto-trait implementations and blanket implementations."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../docs/limitations.rst:18
msgid "Types determined through macro evaluation."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../docs/limitations.rst:19
msgid "Array lengths, except when defined using literals."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../docs/limitations.rst:20
msgid ""
"Const expressions or other expressions that require evaluating Rust code at "
"compile time."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../docs/limitations.rst:21
msgid ""
"Links to items imported with a glob ``use`` statement (e.g. ``use my_crate::"
"*``)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../docs/limitations.rst:23
msgid ""
"Links are only possible to items that are within the same build. :ref:`intra-"
"doc` are supported with minor changes to the docstrings, but only within the "
"same build as well."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../docs/limitations.rst:26
msgid ""
"Also, unlike docs.rs where links are globally generated, Sphinx can only "
"generate links to items defined within the build process. External links can "
"be added in the documentation itself using the RST or MD link syntax."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../docs/limitations.rst:29
msgid ""
"Using RST as the format will certainly not work with other Rust tools and "
"doctests will not execute."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../docs/limitations.rst:31
msgid ""
"Use markdown for compatibility with Rust tooling and see :doc:"
"`compatibility` for any changes required to support the markdown syntax in "
"use."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../docs/limitations.rst:34
msgid "Rustdoc CSS themes cannot be used with Sphinx."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../docs/limitations.rst:36
msgid ""
"Sphinx does its own publication of HTML and so the CSS themes used have to "
"be Sphinx compatible. If someone knows of a CSS theme that is compatible "
"with both Sphinx and rustdoc, please create an issue with a link to the "
"theme and it will be added here."
msgstr ""
